      "writtenOn": "2020-03-26T01:25:40Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "loadMore above seems to ignore this precondition\n\ni think would make more sense to me is\n1) in loadMore, check if loadPromise is null. If it is not null, do nothing\n2) otherwise start the iterator, assign to loadMore, subscribe to it and set loadPromise to null when it is done\n3) make loadMore async, so that the caller, if they want to, know when loadMore is done\n4) document clearly that loadMore is noop if the previous call is done yet\n5) in UI, disable \"load more\" button when clicked, and enable it again when loadMore promise is done",
      "range": {
